In

proximity

fireplace
was
the
kitchen

or
refuse

where
were
found
numbers
of

limpet

oyster

and
cockles,

together,
and
in

several

bones
of
the
ox,
sheep,
pig,
etc.
Intermingled
in
this

heap
were
fragments
of
pottery
of
Roman
manufacture.

Near
this,
also
turned
up
in
the
excavation,
a
rubbing

stone,
which
was
used
for
grinding
corn.

iron
